  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_0",
      "value": "This tool compares a term loan and lease to pay for real estate you will need to operate your business. To compare the value of payments over time for the lease-or-loan option, the calculator shows payments in present value."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_1",
      "value": "A term loan helps you to buy the real estate. While your business pays all expenses, it realizes substantial tax savings from these expenses. As the owner of the real estate, your business also benefits from possible increases in the value of the property. However, loan financing may crimp your cash flow: a down payment is a large initial expenditure, and your monthly payments are larger to include repayment of loan principal. If your business is a young enterprise, you may not have the level of cash necessary to sustain high debt payments."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_2",
      "value": "A lease lets you obtain business real estate at a cost that is generally less than loan financing. Under a lease, your monthly lease payments will be usually lower than loan payments. You also avoid a down payment. Instead, you pay a security deposit that is much smaller than a down payment. When the lease term expires, you have more flexibility than with a loan. You can usually renew the lease or walk away."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_3",
      "value": "Be sure to understand all terms and conditions of the lease agreement. For example, an agreement may include provisions that require operating expenses to rise at a different annual rate than the base rent or in some cases may be in proportion to your sales revenue."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_4",
      "value": "Key assumptions of this tool include:"
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_5",
      "value": "Construction and remodeling costs. If you incur construction or remodeling costs, these costs are added to the loan principal. If you decide to lease, these costs are paid in cash. These costs are added to the basis of the property."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_6",
      "value": "Depreciation. The MACRS depreciation schedule and straight-line depreciation are used. The mid-month convention is used to calculate depreciation expense in the first year, regardless of purchase date."
    }
  },
